WEBVTT

00:59.351 --> 01:01.020
HUGH DOWNS:
Jim and Tammy Faye Bakker

01:01.103 --> 01:04.106
were the most famous
televangelist couple in America,

01:04.273 --> 01:06.192
and, by far, the most prosperous.

01:06.358 --> 01:08.611
AL DALE: Ken and Barbie
of televangelism.

01:08.778 --> 01:10.196
And they seemed honest.

01:10.362 --> 01:12.990
REPORTER 1: They brought encouragement
and hope to lots of people.

01:13.157 --> 01:14.158
GERALDO RIVERA: He's the president

01:14.241 --> 01:15.785
of a multi-million dollar
religious organization

01:15.951 --> 01:17.578
called the Praise The Lord Club.

01:17.745 --> 01:19.872
REPORTER 2: PTL also
operates Heritage Village

01:19.955 --> 01:21.540
in Fort Mill, South Carolina.

01:21.624 --> 01:22.833
REPORTER 3: ...Christian Disney World

01:22.958 --> 01:25.503
where PTL members
can vacation with inspiration.

01:25.669 --> 01:27.296
They are among the best-known figures

01:27.379 --> 01:28.923
in the world of television evangelism.

01:29.089 --> 01:31.133
But tonight they are out of business.

01:31.217 --> 01:32.468
...following the scandal that led

01:32.551 --> 01:34.303
to founder Jim Bakker's
resignation last week.

01:34.470 --> 01:37.014
There's debate about
how much the Bakker scandal will hurt

01:37.181 --> 01:39.350
all the television ministries
and quiet concern...

01:39.517 --> 01:41.352
Modern warfare among the TV preachers.

01:41.560 --> 01:43.521
In this electronic age,
the stakes are high

01:43.604 --> 01:45.022
-with millions of followers...
-...and recriminations.

01:45.105 --> 01:46.106
And caught up in the fighting

01:46.190 --> 01:47.775
are their fellow evangelists
Jimmy Swaggart,

01:47.942 --> 01:49.276
Oral Roberts, Jerry Falwell.

01:49.443 --> 01:50.778
Now, about what some people around here

01:50.861 --> 01:52.112
are calling "pearly-gate."

01:52.279 --> 01:54.949
Pearly-gate is the story
of Jim and Tammy Bakker.

01:55.115 --> 01:56.867
It's remarkably like Watergate,

01:56.951 --> 02:00.246
which tainted the name "politician,"

02:00.412 --> 02:05.501
and such an episode is bound
to taint the name "preacher."

02:05.584 --> 02:07.711
REPORTER 4: The Bakkers
couldn't even get out of their car.

02:07.795 --> 02:09.171
There were so many people
waiting to see them

02:09.255 --> 02:10.256
after three months of seclusion.

02:10.339 --> 02:11.632
REPORTER 5: ...busloads of tourists,

02:11.715 --> 02:13.968
hoping to get a glimpse
of the elusive evangelists,

02:14.134 --> 02:16.637
but they had no better luck
than the waiting newspeople.

02:20.975 --> 02:23.936
WOMAN: Okay, I'm gonna start
by taking some of this off.

02:24.103 --> 02:25.312
TAMMY: Okay.

02:25.479 --> 02:27.147
WOMAN: Gonna take your foundation off.

02:27.231 --> 02:28.232
TAMMY: M'kay.

02:28.440 --> 02:30.401
WOMAN: And then we'll start fresh.

02:31.235 --> 02:32.695
Can you take your lips off?

02:39.535 --> 02:41.120
-Okay.
-Do you want a little remover?

02:41.287 --> 02:44.290
Oh, no. That's it.

02:45.040 --> 02:46.917
That'll be all.
They're permanently lined.

02:47.084 --> 02:48.335
WOMAN: Oh.

02:48.502 --> 02:50.045
And my eyes are permanently lined

02:50.129 --> 02:51.797
and my eyebrows are permanently on,

02:51.964 --> 02:54.675
so there's not a whole lot
you can do.

02:54.758 --> 02:56.010
WOMAN: My goodness,

02:56.093 --> 02:57.553
-I... I didn't know.
-Mm.

02:58.178 --> 02:59.972
Have you never done pictures
without those eyelashes?

03:00.139 --> 03:01.223
Nope, and I never will

03:01.390 --> 03:02.766
because that's my trademark.

03:02.933 --> 03:06.270
And, you know, if I take that away,
then it's not me,

03:06.478 --> 03:08.272
and no one's gonna wanna look
at me without my trademark.

03:08.439 --> 03:09.648
So, I hold onto that.

03:09.815 --> 03:11.275
Even if we softened 'em up and kept...

03:11.442 --> 03:14.111
No. No, you can do anything you want,

03:14.278 --> 03:16.906
but my eyelashes stay
right where they are.

03:17.072 --> 03:18.657
WOMAN: That's really you.

03:18.741 --> 03:19.742
TAMMY: Mm.

03:20.117 --> 03:22.620
Oh, yeah, this is who I am.

03:38.677 --> 03:41.722
PREACHER: I didn't know
what the words "glory" or "hallelujah" be

03:41.889 --> 03:43.682
because the devil is all around us!

03:43.766 --> 03:44.934
-Oh, yes, he is!

03:45.017 --> 03:47.519
And it's up to you to resist
his temptations. Hallelujah!

03:48.729 --> 03:50.356
If you're not saved by Jesus,

03:50.439 --> 03:52.524
you open yourself up to demons

03:52.691 --> 03:55.736
and the devil will make a home in you!

03:56.195 --> 03:57.196
WOMAN: Glory to God!

03:57.279 --> 03:58.781
When God spoke peace to my heart,

03:58.948 --> 04:01.450
I didn't know how to say glory
or hallelujah,

04:01.617 --> 04:03.202
but I got saved!

04:03.369 --> 04:04.954
I leapt upon that altar.

04:05.120 --> 04:07.081
Jesus told me He loved me,

04:07.247 --> 04:09.792
and He will love you.

04:11.001 --> 04:13.837
He speaks through her.
Say, "Hallelujah!"

04:14.004 --> 04:15.589
CONGREGATION: Hallelujah!

04:15.756 --> 04:18.509
PREACHER: She is with
the Holy Spirit right now!

04:18.676 --> 04:20.594
Feel the spirit! Say, "Glory.

04:21.220 --> 04:22.388
"Glory to God."

04:22.554 --> 04:23.722
CONGREGATION: Glory to God!

04:23.889 --> 04:26.475
PREACHER: You too, sister!
Feel the spirit.

04:26.642 --> 04:28.352
Raise your hands up, folks.

04:30.479 --> 04:31.939
LITTLE TAMMY: I was here.

04:32.106 --> 04:33.232
Here the whole time.

04:33.732 --> 04:35.901
Little girls go to Hell for lying.

04:36.276 --> 04:37.820
Honest and true.

04:37.987 --> 04:39.446
I wanna be saved.

04:40.948 --> 04:42.282
If you let me come in with you,

04:42.366 --> 04:44.410
God'd love me like He's supposed to.

04:44.576 --> 04:46.328
There's reasons
you can't be seen in church, Tam.

04:46.495 --> 04:47.830
Grown-up reasons.

04:48.414 --> 04:50.499
Is it because everyone thinks
you're a harlot?

04:52.459 --> 04:53.460
And I come from a time

04:53.544 --> 04:55.170
before Fred made you
respectable and stuff.

04:57.339 --> 04:58.924
Only reason they let me back

04:59.008 --> 05:01.135
is 'cause nobody but me
can play the piano.

05:01.343 --> 05:03.804
But you remind them I was divorced.

05:04.054 --> 05:06.056
They see you,

05:06.223 --> 05:07.933
all of us is going to be banished.

05:09.351 --> 05:11.270
The souls of all your brothers and sisters

05:11.437 --> 05:13.897
burning in Hell because you don't listen

05:13.981 --> 05:15.941
and you can't sit still.

05:22.698 --> 05:24.241
Stop performing.

05:28.245 --> 05:30.247
You're going to Hell, Tammy.

05:30.414 --> 05:33.667
You don't belong here.
You don't belong anywhere.

05:33.834 --> 05:35.294
You're ugly.

05:35.461 --> 05:37.296
You've got a demon inside you.

05:38.464 --> 05:40.466
But I don't wanna go to Hell.

05:41.508 --> 05:42.968
If they loved you,

05:43.052 --> 05:44.720
they wouldn't leave you here.

05:45.721 --> 05:46.847
They love me.

05:47.014 --> 05:49.224
They love you not.

05:52.603 --> 05:55.355
Jesus, come into my heart

05:55.439 --> 05:57.316
and forgive me my sins.

05:58.317 --> 06:01.445
I don't know what this is
everybody's getting,

06:01.612 --> 06:02.780
but if it's real,

06:03.405 --> 06:06.909
then, please, Jesus, give that to me.

06:09.286 --> 06:10.704
-PREACHER: Amen!

06:11.288 --> 06:13.957
Be strong in the Lord
and His mighty power.

06:14.124 --> 06:15.459
Put on the armor of God

06:15.626 --> 06:16.752
so that you can take your stand

06:16.835 --> 06:18.545
against the devil's schemes.

06:18.712 --> 06:21.507
For our struggle isn't
against flesh and blood,

06:21.673 --> 06:24.593
but against the powers
of this dark world!

06:24.760 --> 06:26.470
Casting down imaginations

06:26.637 --> 06:30.140
on every high thing that exalts itself.

06:30.307 --> 06:32.101
-Do you feel love?
-CONGREGATION: Yes.

06:32.309 --> 06:34.228
PREACHER: You feel it, sister!
I know you feel it!

06:35.354 --> 06:36.939
You too, brother?

06:37.231 --> 06:38.649
If you feel the love,

06:38.732 --> 06:40.400
-say, "Hallelujah!"
-CONGREGATION: Hallelujah!

06:40.484 --> 06:42.861
PREACHER: Say, "Glory to God!"
CONGREGATION: Glory to God!

06:43.237 --> 06:44.404
PREACHER: Accept the blood!

06:44.613 --> 06:46.156
Feel love forever!

06:46.323 --> 06:47.407
CONGREGATION: Hallelujah!

06:47.491 --> 06:48.951
WOMAN: Praise the Lord!

06:49.535 --> 06:51.161
Are you ready to accept the love?

06:51.745 --> 06:52.871
Yes.

07:07.761 --> 07:08.929
Tammy Faye!

07:11.181 --> 07:14.351
I'm so sorry. I'm so, so sorry.

07:16.103 --> 07:17.855
No, Tammy!

07:18.230 --> 07:20.190
Tammy, get up.

07:20.732 --> 07:21.942
He is with us!

07:22.734 --> 07:24.611
She's peeing herself! Praise God!

07:25.154 --> 07:26.155
Yes!

07:26.613 --> 07:28.448
-Tammy, I said get up.
-WOMAN: Shush now.

07:28.824 --> 07:31.702
This baby is a miracle.
Don't you take her from us.

07:37.541 --> 07:38.834
MAN: Mr. Bakker?

07:39.376 --> 07:40.460
JIM: Yes, sir?

07:42.880 --> 07:43.922
Thank you.

07:51.471 --> 07:53.807
Um, sorry.

07:56.226 --> 07:57.519
I would like to start with a verse.

07:58.145 --> 08:03.525
"Beloved, I wish above all things
that thou mayest prosper

08:03.692 --> 08:07.613
"and be in health,
even as thy soul prospereth."

08:07.779 --> 08:09.281
That is John 3, verse 2,

08:09.364 --> 08:12.034
and it's written right here
in the good book.

08:12.201 --> 08:14.244
He gave me this verse last night.

08:14.411 --> 08:17.247
God, He came right down
and He whispered it in my ear.

08:17.414 --> 08:18.999
He said, "Jim Bakker,

08:19.166 --> 08:22.502
"I intend for you to thrive,

08:22.669 --> 08:25.088
"to live, and to love

08:25.255 --> 08:27.090
"in this life."

08:27.257 --> 08:28.258
He said it to me.

08:28.425 --> 08:29.885
But us Christians,

08:30.761 --> 08:33.430
we've been taught
that we're supposed to

08:33.889 --> 08:36.391
expect failure.

08:37.976 --> 08:39.353
-When Jesus calls you home,

08:39.436 --> 08:40.938
you think you're going to get a bonus

08:41.021 --> 08:43.106
if you make yourself miserable?

08:44.274 --> 08:46.318
You think if you deny yourself
indoor plumbing,

08:46.485 --> 08:47.903
or if you don't have shoes

08:47.986 --> 08:49.863
-on your feet...
-

08:51.031 --> 08:52.491
I'm... I'm sorry.

08:55.744 --> 08:56.745
Go ahead.

08:59.790 --> 09:01.333
You know, Heaven,

09:01.416 --> 09:03.335
Heaven is heaven, that is for sure.

09:03.502 --> 09:06.004
But God's hope for us

09:06.171 --> 09:09.967
is that we live and we thrive
and we love here

09:10.133 --> 09:11.260
in the promised land.

09:11.426 --> 09:12.844
Here and now.

09:13.011 --> 09:16.890
Here and now,
and in this very, very moment.

09:16.974 --> 09:18.225
Hallelujah!

09:18.308 --> 09:20.769
God does not want us to be poor!

09:20.978 --> 09:22.104
Oh, no!

09:22.813 --> 09:26.066
He will gift the faithful
with eternal life,

09:26.233 --> 09:29.236
eternal love, and eternal wealth!

09:29.403 --> 09:33.073
Hallelujah! Praise God!
Praise Him!

09:36.034 --> 09:37.369
Be right to remember,

09:37.452 --> 09:39.913
"Blessed be the poor," Mr. Bakker.

09:40.080 --> 09:42.207
Doesn't sound very blessed to me.

09:45.669 --> 09:49.339
You two are here to learn the ways
of the Lord through scripture, yeah?

09:49.423 --> 09:50.424
Yes, sir.

09:50.507 --> 09:51.508
And to spread the word of God.

09:51.591 --> 09:52.592
Oh, yeah. You know,

09:52.676 --> 09:54.845
I'm gonna sing the word in every tent,
in every church.

09:55.012 --> 09:57.848
You know, God told me that
that's what He wants for me.

09:59.766 --> 10:01.560
With makeup on your face?

10:02.811 --> 10:04.813
Ahem. Jezebel.
-

10:10.277 --> 10:12.029
"I do my best to maintain always

10:12.112 --> 10:13.155
"a blameless conscience,

10:13.238 --> 10:15.490
"both before God and before men."

10:17.534 --> 10:19.661
"A man who keeps company with harlots

10:20.912 --> 10:22.289
"wastes his wealth."

10:22.456 --> 10:24.750
Proverbs 29:3.

10:24.916 --> 10:28.587
"Your stature is like that of a palm
and your breasts

10:29.212 --> 10:30.547
"like clusters of fruit.

10:30.630 --> 10:32.674
"I will take hold of the palm tree."

10:32.841 --> 10:36.303
"And I will take hold of the fruit."

10:37.512 --> 10:39.014
That's the Song of Solomon.

10:39.181 --> 10:41.224
7:7.

10:45.020 --> 10:47.814
JIM: I'm sorry I couldn't
drive you someplace nice.

10:48.190 --> 10:50.650
Oh, this is someplace nice, Jim.

10:51.693 --> 10:53.362
Tell me something. Tell me a secret.

10:53.528 --> 10:55.072
Something that no one else knows about.

10:55.238 --> 10:56.239
Oh, I have no secrets.

10:56.323 --> 10:57.532
I'll tell you anything you wanna know.

10:57.699 --> 10:58.867
We'll start with everything.

11:00.827 --> 11:02.412
-Okay.
-

11:02.579 --> 11:03.789
I'm the oldest of eight children

11:03.872 --> 11:05.624
and I'm a very practical person.

11:05.791 --> 11:07.250
And what you see is all there is of me.

11:07.417 --> 11:08.960
You know, I don't pretend
to be something I'm not

11:09.127 --> 11:10.670
because what you see is all you get.

11:10.837 --> 11:12.255
And I love people.

11:12.631 --> 11:15.759
I have a genuine,
genuine love for people.

11:16.009 --> 11:18.178
And I hurt when people hurt,

11:18.345 --> 11:20.555
and probably a little more dramatic
than people would like me to be.

11:20.639 --> 11:23.475
But I enjoy that.
That's just who I am.

11:24.643 --> 11:27.104
I've never met anyone quite like you,
Tammy Faye.

11:29.940 --> 11:31.108
Okay.

11:31.274 --> 11:34.569
So, um, do you have any secrets, Jim?

11:35.529 --> 11:38.198
Well, one or two.

11:39.074 --> 11:40.826
Well, tell me.

11:40.992 --> 11:45.122
Well, before God found me,
I wanted to be a radio deejay.

11:46.665 --> 11:47.833
-No.
-Yes.

11:48.708 --> 11:52.087
I used to love to make people dance.

11:52.254 --> 11:53.422
Have fun.

11:54.172 --> 11:56.299
-Little Richard.
-

11:56.466 --> 11:58.009
And Buddy Holly and...

11:58.677 --> 12:00.137
Oh, and Fats Domino.

12:02.180 --> 12:04.099
What happened?
Why didn't you do it, Jim?

12:04.182 --> 12:05.225
Ah.

12:06.017 --> 12:07.644
Never mind that.

12:07.811 --> 12:08.812
Tell me.

12:10.063 --> 12:12.107
Um, I don't think...

12:14.693 --> 12:17.446
Well, all right.
I'll tell you, Tammy. Um...

12:18.029 --> 12:20.073
Two years ago,
I was on a date

12:20.157 --> 12:21.533
with my girlfriend, Sandy, and...

12:21.616 --> 12:22.784
Mm.
-Oh, no,

12:22.868 --> 12:24.327
with my girlfriend at the time.

12:24.744 --> 12:26.204
-Mm.
-But, anyhoo,

12:26.288 --> 12:27.664
I borrowed my daddy's car
to take her out,

12:27.747 --> 12:31.251
and there was all this snow
on the ground

12:31.877 --> 12:36.298
and Fats was singing Blueberry Hill

12:36.465 --> 12:37.757
so loud

12:39.426 --> 12:41.219
and I... I was having these urges

12:41.303 --> 12:43.472
that only the devil would approve of

12:43.638 --> 12:46.349
and I lost control of the car.

12:49.728 --> 12:51.813
And I ran over a little boy,

12:52.397 --> 12:53.899
-little Jimmy Summerfield.
-

12:54.983 --> 12:57.068
I ruptured Jimmy Summerfield's lung...

12:57.152 --> 12:59.529
-...with my daddy's tire.

12:59.696 --> 13:00.906
I didn't sleep all night.

13:01.072 --> 13:03.742
I was just up worried sick
about that boy dying.

13:03.825 --> 13:04.826
So, I...

13:05.452 --> 13:07.078
I made a bargain with God.

13:07.412 --> 13:08.872
I said to Him,

13:09.039 --> 13:11.208
"I will forsake my dream
of being a deejay.

13:11.374 --> 13:15.962
"I will stop peddling in rock and roll

13:16.129 --> 13:20.342
"and I'll dedicate my life
to Him and Him alone.

13:20.509 --> 13:23.261
"If He sees fit to save that boy's life,

13:23.428 --> 13:26.848
"He will win two souls
right then and there."

13:28.892 --> 13:30.727
And what happened to Jimmy Summerfield?

13:31.728 --> 13:32.812
He lived.

13:32.896 --> 13:34.189
-Oh.
-Yes.

13:34.356 --> 13:36.316
-Praise be to God.
-Yes, praise Him.

13:39.110 --> 13:40.278
So...

13:42.113 --> 13:43.740
You still like me?

13:44.199 --> 13:46.785
Oh, sure, I do, Jim.

13:47.160 --> 13:50.413
Oh, even more now that
you were honest with me.

13:52.749 --> 13:54.000
I'll tell ya, I do miss dancing.

13:56.920 --> 13:59.923
I found my thrill

14:01.466 --> 14:05.095
On Blueberry Hill

14:06.263 --> 14:09.391
I found my thrill

14:11.059 --> 14:14.062
When I found you

14:14.229 --> 14:15.480
You're so loud.

14:16.231 --> 14:17.357
Dance with me, Jim.

14:18.066 --> 14:19.276
Here? No, I can't.

14:19.442 --> 14:21.778
In front of all these people?
Like, no...

14:21.945 --> 14:23.071
Please?

14:26.825 --> 14:30.328
The moon stood still

14:30.495 --> 14:34.249
On Blueberry Hill

14:34.499 --> 14:38.253
-And lingered until
-

14:39.212 --> 14:42.924
My dreams came true

14:51.349 --> 14:53.018
Oh, we can't.

14:53.226 --> 14:54.436
I know.

15:00.400 --> 15:01.985
-We can't.
-I know.

15:05.822 --> 15:09.117
Oh. Oh, we can't.

15:11.161 --> 15:12.162
I know.

15:16.458 --> 15:17.500
Yeah!

15:19.544 --> 15:20.754
What'd you do?

15:21.046 --> 15:23.506
Hello, Mother.
This is Jim Bakker,

15:27.677 --> 15:32.098
Oh, it's such a blessing
to finally meet you.

15:39.314 --> 15:40.315
TAMMY: No.

15:40.482 --> 15:41.858
No, Mother, we can't go back to school.

15:42.025 --> 15:44.319
They have a rule against
students marrying one another.

15:44.486 --> 15:46.196
Did you know they had that rule
when you did this?

15:46.363 --> 15:49.282
If I know the two of you,
you're just gonna love Jim.

15:49.449 --> 15:50.617
Oh, he's so motivated.

15:50.784 --> 15:52.410
He has so many big ideas.

15:52.577 --> 15:53.995
Did you know?

16:05.215 --> 16:08.385
Well, you can educate yourself
right out of a relationship with God.

16:08.551 --> 16:10.011
He has a plan for us.

16:10.470 --> 16:13.014
-God or that Jim boy?
-God.

16:13.848 --> 16:15.475
What'd He tell ya to do this time?

16:15.642 --> 16:19.270
Come spring, me and Jim
are going to be traveling preachers,

16:19.437 --> 16:20.897
bringing God's love to all people.

16:21.064 --> 16:23.858
Anyone who's hurting
or they feel like they've been left out.

16:24.025 --> 16:25.777
Jim will preach and I'll sing.

16:25.944 --> 16:28.530
And we'll be like
Oral Roberts and his wife.

16:29.280 --> 16:31.282
Oral Roberts went to college.

16:31.574 --> 16:34.452
-He has one named for him.

16:34.619 --> 16:36.538
God said that we're supposed
to have a good life.

16:36.705 --> 16:38.998
That way, we can help
bring his love to all people.

16:39.165 --> 16:41.751
There's a limit to God's love,
Tammy Faye.

16:42.752 --> 16:43.753
TAMMY AND JIM: No.

16:44.045 --> 16:48.091
No, there's no limit to God's love,
Mrs. Grover,

16:48.299 --> 16:50.802
and there's no limit
to Tammy Faye and I either.

16:51.428 --> 16:52.887
We're soldiers in Christ.

16:53.054 --> 16:55.724
We've been called to serve
in a very real way.

16:55.890 --> 16:57.809
God smiles on a husband and wife.

16:57.976 --> 17:00.311
"As a young man marries a young woman,

17:00.478 --> 17:02.897
"so will your Builder marry you;

17:03.064 --> 17:06.651
"as a bridegroom rejoices in his bride,

17:06.818 --> 17:09.738
"so will your God rejoice in you."

17:09.904 --> 17:11.614
Isaiah 62:5.

17:14.576 --> 17:16.286
JIM: It's something we do.

17:28.715 --> 17:31.384
Fred said that we could stay
until the weather changes.

17:33.011 --> 17:34.262
Got some bubbles at the swap meet.

17:39.309 --> 17:41.186
I'm sorry, Tam.

17:43.021 --> 17:45.064
I feel like I'm letting you down.

17:46.232 --> 17:48.777
She doesn't like me.

17:49.110 --> 17:51.696
-No, Jim.
-No, she doesn't.

17:52.864 --> 17:55.033
Of course she likes you.

17:58.369 --> 17:59.496
TAMMY: Oh.

18:04.167 --> 18:07.629
It makes Tammy sad
to see you so sad.

18:09.172 --> 18:10.548
How's there supposed to be bubbles

18:10.632 --> 18:13.092
if there isn't enough water
to work up the bubbles?

18:13.259 --> 18:15.970
Oh, I can work up the bubbles, Jim.

18:16.304 --> 18:19.432
All I gotta do is dunk my hand.

18:21.643 --> 18:24.145
And I swirl...

18:29.526 --> 18:31.486
-And swirl.
-

18:32.654 --> 18:34.656
-

18:37.325 --> 18:38.701
-Am I doing that all right?

18:38.868 --> 18:40.370
Uh-huh.

18:53.174 --> 18:55.593
Well, hello there, Tammy Faye.

18:57.303 --> 18:58.888
Hello, Mommy.

18:59.055 --> 19:00.890
What are you doing with those things?

19:01.057 --> 19:03.059
Well, we're gonna use these
puppets as part of our sermon

19:03.226 --> 19:04.894
and show the kids how wonderful God is.

19:05.061 --> 19:06.563
And if we can get enough children to come,

19:06.729 --> 19:08.064
they'll bring their mothers
and their fathers.

19:08.147 --> 19:10.275
And before you know it,
we'll have our own church.

19:14.904 --> 19:17.740
Have you counted
your blessings today, Tammy Faye?

19:17.907 --> 19:19.826
No, not yet, Susie.

19:20.159 --> 19:23.204
Time to count your blessings,
for they are plentiful.

19:23.788 --> 19:27.166
Okay, well, thank you for my husband.

19:27.333 --> 19:30.753
Oh, you're so welcome, Tammy.

19:31.504 --> 19:35.008
And thank you for Mother's understanding,
even if she doesn't understand.

19:35.675 --> 19:38.136
You're welcome.

19:39.929 --> 19:42.348
And thank you, God, for love.

19:59.616 --> 20:00.617
Hmm.

20:00.700 --> 20:02.660
-

20:03.036 --> 20:05.455
-

20:07.248 --> 20:10.209
Jim! Whose car is this?

20:11.669 --> 20:12.962
No.

20:13.296 --> 20:16.174
-Get in. Get in. Come on.

20:16.341 --> 20:17.425
TAMMY: Okay.

20:18.343 --> 20:20.345
Roll that window up.
I got the heat on.

20:21.554 --> 20:22.972
This fine vehicle

20:23.056 --> 20:25.892
with the leather interior
and the chrome on the wheels

20:26.059 --> 20:29.771
is a gift from God
for us to do His work.

20:33.024 --> 20:35.526
But how
can we afford it, Jim Bakker?

20:36.861 --> 20:38.488
Who is this?

20:38.655 --> 20:40.031
I'm Susie Moppet.

20:40.198 --> 20:43.493
Aren't you cute? Well, do
you know about God, Susie?

20:43.701 --> 20:44.702
Oh, I do.

20:44.786 --> 20:48.081
Well, God has cancelled
the claim of poverty

20:48.164 --> 20:49.832
and deprivation in our lives

20:49.999 --> 20:52.669
and He has placed
all the powers of heaven

20:52.835 --> 20:55.088
and the First Bank
of International Falls,

20:55.171 --> 20:57.548
Minnesota, at our disposal.

21:03.638 --> 21:06.933
Oh, this is the nicest car
I've ever seen, Jim.

21:07.141 --> 21:10.103
"Everything works for good
for them that love God."

21:10.186 --> 21:11.729
Everything.

21:12.230 --> 21:15.149
But you have
to have faith in Him

21:15.316 --> 21:18.236
and in me and in us,
'cause if you don't,

21:18.403 --> 21:20.029
I don't know
what I'm doing here.

21:20.196 --> 21:22.198
-Oh, I do, Jim.
-You do?

21:24.367 --> 21:25.660
Does she, Susie?

21:26.869 --> 21:28.371
Oh, she do, Jim!

21:28.538 --> 21:31.207
-She really, really do!
-

21:41.259 --> 21:43.011
JIM: You sure...

21:43.177 --> 21:45.763
It's all right here.
In Psalm 37:4.

21:45.847 --> 21:47.890
"Take delight in the Lord

21:48.057 --> 21:51.978
"and He will give you
your heart's desires."

21:52.145 --> 21:55.648
God starts turning
those wheels in your life!

21:55.815 --> 21:56.983
SUSIE: You better believe it!

21:57.150 --> 21:59.652
-JIM: Oh, now who is this?
-Oh, I'm Susie Moppet.

21:59.861 --> 22:01.362
Well, hello there, Susie Moppet.

22:01.529 --> 22:02.947
SUSIE: Hi! Nice to meet you!

22:04.490 --> 22:06.743
-She jumped up.
-

22:07.744 --> 22:09.537
Yes, Jesus loves me

22:09.704 --> 22:11.289
Yes, Jesus loves me

22:11.456 --> 22:12.915
Yes, Jesus loves me

22:13.082 --> 22:16.794
BOTH: The Bible tells me so

22:16.961 --> 22:19.297
Hitch up your wagon to God.

22:19.505 --> 22:21.257
He's greater than any problem.

22:21.424 --> 22:22.759
Us Christians, we're just
stuck in the mud

22:22.925 --> 22:24.761
like that old game.
Remember that old kids' game?

22:24.927 --> 22:27.096
God wants us just to run free.

22:31.476 --> 22:33.352
Well, this is a fun song,
boys and girls.

22:33.519 --> 22:34.687
So, hit it, Allie.

22:35.146 --> 22:36.314
Jesus loves me

22:36.397 --> 22:39.108
This I know
For the Bible tells me so

22:39.400 --> 22:41.360
Yes, Jesus loves me

22:41.527 --> 22:44.030
-ALLIE: The Bible tells me so
-

22:47.283 --> 22:49.118
ANNOUNCER:
You're watching Pat Robertson

22:49.202 --> 22:50.828
on the Christian
Broadcasting Network.

22:50.995 --> 22:51.996
JIM: Come on.

22:52.080 --> 22:54.165
Season all your grain offerings...

22:54.332 --> 22:55.750
Oh, come on!

22:55.833 --> 22:58.044
-Okay, okay, okay.
-...with salt.

22:58.211 --> 23:01.172
Do not leave the salt
of the covenant of your God

23:01.255 --> 23:03.132
out of your grain offerings.

23:03.216 --> 23:04.509
Add salt

23:05.218 --> 23:06.469
to all your offerings.

23:06.552 --> 23:09.972
You know, he's not terribly
dynamic for a charismatic.

23:10.139 --> 23:11.641
JIM: I know, but people just eat him up.

23:11.849 --> 23:14.227
...focus on the foundation.

23:14.435 --> 23:15.895
-Tammy, did you see that?
-Hmm?

23:15.978 --> 23:18.272
Watch close.
Every now and again,

23:18.439 --> 23:20.358
he glances up at the camera.

23:20.525 --> 23:23.486
It is upon Him that you
can place your strong...

23:23.653 --> 23:25.113
-See that?
- You're right.

23:25.196 --> 23:28.783
He's talking right to you
in the comfort of your living room.

23:28.950 --> 23:31.035
Well, if I could have watched a preacher

23:31.202 --> 23:34.288
on TV in my own home telling me about God,

23:34.455 --> 23:36.332
that would've made such a difference.

23:36.415 --> 23:38.334
JIM: Mm. Amen.

23:38.918 --> 23:42.630
Especially from someone
who preaches as good as you do, Jim.

23:43.339 --> 23:45.508
-

23:45.591 --> 23:47.218
-You think?
-Oh, yeah.

23:47.385 --> 23:49.428
...blow your home over?

23:50.012 --> 23:51.430
You know, we could do that.

23:53.099 --> 23:56.435
You're so much more handsome than he is.

23:57.687 --> 23:58.729
Keep calling.

23:58.938 --> 24:00.148
JIM: Gotta do my homework, baby.

24:00.231 --> 24:01.315
The numbers are on your screen.

24:01.399 --> 24:02.733
Mm. Stop it.

24:02.900 --> 24:04.694
You're distracting me.

24:04.861 --> 24:07.363
...voices of angels.
I hope you enjoy them,

24:07.446 --> 24:08.656
and we have a variety...

24:09.448 --> 24:12.451
Well, we'll have to call the preacher
down in Raleigh

24:12.618 --> 24:14.328
and let him know we got
a better gig down here.

24:14.495 --> 24:16.247
Don't make him cross at you, Jim.

24:16.414 --> 24:18.082
We wanna have him want us back.

24:18.249 --> 24:19.625
JIM: Hold on.

24:19.792 --> 24:21.085
TAMMY: What?

24:21.252 --> 24:22.336
JIM: The car.

24:23.546 --> 24:24.672
I...

24:26.340 --> 24:27.967
I... I parked it here.

24:28.259 --> 24:30.803
Yep, you sure did. Uh-huh.

24:32.263 --> 24:33.389
Well, must've got stolen...

24:33.556 --> 24:34.640
What?

24:34.724 --> 24:36.893
Oh.

24:37.977 --> 24:39.061
Oh, maybe it got towed.

24:39.687 --> 24:42.565
No, I know I made the payments, so...

24:43.983 --> 24:45.526
I think I made the payments.

24:45.693 --> 24:46.694
Oh, Jim.

24:46.777 --> 24:48.362
Maybe they didn't get
the payments or maybe...

24:48.446 --> 24:49.447
Oh, no.

24:49.530 --> 24:50.823
I don't think I forgot.

24:51.199 --> 24:52.533
-I think I...
-Okay.

24:52.617 --> 24:54.952
-Oh, Tammy, I don't know...
-We need to pray.

24:55.119 --> 24:57.163
Oh, did I? Yes, yes, yes.

24:57.246 --> 24:58.414
TAMMY: Oh, Lord,

24:58.581 --> 25:00.374
we are good soldiers.

25:00.541 --> 25:02.168
-We are here for good.
-Oh, I'm sorry, Tammy.

25:02.251 --> 25:03.920
-We are here for your good.
-I'm so, so, so sorry.

25:04.003 --> 25:05.213
And we ask that you shine your light...

25:05.296 --> 25:06.797
JIM: I shouldn't have put
so much faith in that bank.

25:06.881 --> 25:08.341
God, I'm so sorry.

25:08.549 --> 25:09.675
Jesus, I'm so sorry.

25:09.842 --> 25:11.302
Tammy, I'm sorry.

25:11.469 --> 25:12.929
I'm sorry.

25:13.095 --> 25:14.597
-Jim.
-

25:16.849 --> 25:17.850
MAN: Hey.

25:18.392 --> 25:20.728
Hey, I saw you preach last night.

25:20.895 --> 25:23.814
Those puppets of yours filled me. Deeply.

25:23.981 --> 25:25.274
TAMMY: Oh, thank you.

25:25.358 --> 25:26.400
JIM: Thank you.

25:26.567 --> 25:28.027
I'm staying in the room next door.

25:28.527 --> 25:30.696
-Can I help you with that?
- No!

25:30.780 --> 25:32.490
Well, that's very kind of you...

25:33.658 --> 25:36.077
...but we don't rightly know
where we're carrying it to.

25:36.911 --> 25:38.537
I work at a local television station

25:38.704 --> 25:40.873
with a minister by the name
of Mr. Pat Robertson.

25:44.961 --> 25:46.379
He'd get a kick outta you two.

25:51.467 --> 25:54.929
WOMAN 1: Yes, honey,
and that's $25 a pledge.

25:55.012 --> 25:58.391
-WOMAN 2: CBN.

25:58.474 --> 26:00.393
Can I take your pledge?

26:01.811 --> 26:03.729
JIM: Well, I'm trying to focus.

26:05.481 --> 26:07.400
And you're just distracting me.

26:07.566 --> 26:09.860
You make me laugh.
I was happy to find...

26:12.738 --> 26:14.699
JIM: You're so funny, Graham.

26:14.865 --> 26:16.325
-Jim?
-Hey, honey.

26:16.409 --> 26:18.119
Hi, I got a new outfit for the show.

26:18.286 --> 26:20.079
Oh, yes, I love it.

26:20.579 --> 26:22.331
Jim.
-JIM: Yeah?

26:22.498 --> 26:23.499
You didn't even look at me.

26:23.666 --> 26:24.667
JIM: Oh.

26:25.293 --> 26:26.711
I'm sorry, Tam.

26:26.877 --> 26:28.045
Have I ever told you

26:28.129 --> 26:31.799
that I am the luckiest man
on the face of this planet?

26:31.882 --> 26:33.634
-Have I ever told you that?

26:33.718 --> 26:35.678
-Not today.
-Not today, no?

26:35.845 --> 26:37.054
I'm going to tell you something, too,

26:37.138 --> 26:38.723
but I'm not gonna tell you right now.

26:38.889 --> 26:39.890
You're gonna have to wait.

26:40.099 --> 26:41.934
-Yeah.

26:42.685 --> 26:43.936
You just have to.

26:44.353 --> 26:45.688
And there he is.

26:46.188 --> 26:47.273
Every time I try and talk to him,

26:47.356 --> 26:49.400
he just keeps making excuses
not to see me.

26:49.567 --> 26:53.321
Well, my surprise is gonna
make you feel so much better.

26:53.904 --> 26:55.156
I'll be right back.

26:55.323 --> 26:56.365
No, Jim,

26:56.532 --> 26:57.825
-the show's about to start.
-JIM: Hey, Pat!

26:57.908 --> 26:59.952
PAT: Jim! Hey!
JIM: You got a second?

27:01.162 --> 27:03.289
Have you given more thought
to our show idea?

27:03.372 --> 27:04.373
MAN: All right,
let me get you set up.

27:04.457 --> 27:05.791
PAT: Don't you already
have your hands full

27:05.875 --> 27:07.084
with those puppets?

27:07.251 --> 27:09.503
Biggest earner we got.
You stay focused.

27:09.670 --> 27:10.755
JIM: Well, yes, of course,

27:10.880 --> 27:13.424
but you shut down CBN at 10 p.m.

27:13.632 --> 27:15.009
Why not do a late-night show?

27:15.176 --> 27:16.969
Just kind of like Johnny Carson
for Christians?

27:17.053 --> 27:19.263
No, Christians don't stay up that late.

27:19.347 --> 27:20.348
Oh, I do.

27:20.431 --> 27:22.016
-I don't sleep at all.
-PAT: What about Tam?

27:22.183 --> 27:23.976
Well, she's gonna miss you at night.

27:24.143 --> 27:26.062
JIM: Tammy loves the idea.
MAN: Tammy, we're on.

27:26.228 --> 27:29.231
MAN 2: Okay, we're live
in five, four, three.

27:33.361 --> 27:34.820
Oh, hello, everybody!

27:34.987 --> 27:37.615
CHILDREN: Hi, Tammy!

27:37.782 --> 27:40.159
Well, Jim is a little bit late today,

27:40.326 --> 27:42.995
so, um, the theme of today's show,

27:43.162 --> 27:44.872
how about we make it
all about the importance

27:44.955 --> 27:47.249
of being places on time, hmm?

27:47.333 --> 27:49.335
Oh, no! Oh, no!
-

27:49.418 --> 27:51.212
-I'm sorry, kids!
-There he is.

27:51.379 --> 27:54.548
I'm sorry, Tammy!
I'm sorry, everybody.

27:54.757 --> 27:57.051
I was just having a little,
fun little chat

27:57.218 --> 27:59.804
with Uncle Pat just behind the barn.

27:59.970 --> 28:02.014
Oh, yeah, and what'd you two
fellas get up to without me?

28:02.181 --> 28:05.101
Oh, well, it's actually
something all you kids...

28:05.184 --> 28:06.185
-Mm-hmm.
-...are gonna wanna

28:06.268 --> 28:07.686
tell your parents about.

28:07.853 --> 28:12.191
It's a brand-new show just for them

28:12.358 --> 28:15.820
right here on CBN!

28:15.903 --> 28:17.363
-Well, amen!

28:17.446 --> 28:20.408
JIM: And it's gonna be called
The 700 Club.

28:20.574 --> 28:22.159
TAMMY: Now, isn't that happy news?

28:22.326 --> 28:25.121
Hallelujah! Yes! Yes!

28:25.287 --> 28:26.288
-SUSIE: Hi, kids.
-Oh.

28:26.705 --> 28:29.917
-ALL: Hi, Susie Moppet.

28:30.084 --> 28:32.711
Hi, Jim.
Today's a happy day.

28:32.878 --> 28:34.380
Isn't it, kids?
And you know why, Jim?

28:34.588 --> 28:36.173
Why, Susie?

28:36.340 --> 28:39.343
Well, you're gonna have
a new show, kids.

28:39.427 --> 28:41.053
-JIM: Yes.
-

28:41.220 --> 28:44.682
SUSIE: And Jim is gonna have

28:44.849 --> 28:46.392
a baby.

28:46.475 --> 28:47.685
-

28:47.768 --> 28:49.645
Look at Tammy,
she's right behind you.

28:53.190 --> 28:54.859
We're gonna have a baby?

28:55.693 --> 28:58.195
Isn't the world just
full of blessings, Jim?

28:58.279 --> 29:00.239
-Huh?

29:00.322 --> 29:02.116
-That's right, folks!

29:05.453 --> 29:07.329
We're gonna have a baby!

29:07.413 --> 29:08.747
-Oh-ho-ho!

29:08.873 --> 29:11.834
JIM: It's not a drag to be saved.

29:12.001 --> 29:13.752
It's not a boring thing.

29:13.919 --> 29:16.672
That's religion.
See, you got 'em mixed up.

29:16.839 --> 29:19.175
Religion is boring and dull,

29:19.341 --> 29:22.511
-but Jesus is life.
-

29:22.678 --> 29:25.222
Now, my next guest is
a new friend to The 700 Club,

29:25.389 --> 29:29.351
and I can smell his chicken,
yes.

29:29.560 --> 29:34.064
The Colonel, Colonel Sanders
in The 700 Club!

29:34.148 --> 29:36.567
-

29:41.280 --> 29:45.409
Oh, the crowd appreciates you.
I think they like you.

29:45.576 --> 29:47.286
I think they're wanting
some of that chicken.

29:47.453 --> 29:48.746
JIM: I guess
the housewives of America

29:48.829 --> 29:50.122
are thanking you for fixing dinner...

29:53.417 --> 29:54.418
Hello.

29:54.585 --> 29:56.003
TAMMY: Oh, hi, Mom.

29:56.170 --> 29:59.340
Do you know what time it is?
Why are you calling so late?

29:59.548 --> 30:02.259
Well, Jim says that I need
to rest for my pregnancy,

30:02.426 --> 30:05.804
but, oh, you know me. I can't rest,

30:05.971 --> 30:08.057
so thought I'd call my mother
to keep me company.

30:08.224 --> 30:10.017
I never got a rest.

30:10.184 --> 30:12.269
Oh, I miss working, though.
You know?

30:12.436 --> 30:15.189
It's so lonesome at home all by myself.

30:15.356 --> 30:17.775
Wow! Oh, wow!

30:17.942 --> 30:19.276
And he barely touches me anymore.

30:19.360 --> 30:21.779
And when he does, it's not enthusiastic.

30:23.239 --> 30:26.700
Well, it's up to the wife
to make herself desirable for her husband.

30:26.867 --> 30:29.328
I do that. Oh, I do.

30:29.828 --> 30:31.872
He's just really busy.

30:32.039 --> 30:33.582
-JIM: Really?
-

30:33.749 --> 30:35.834
So, are you watching Jim's show?

30:36.001 --> 30:38.087
That new talk show of his is on.

30:38.254 --> 30:39.630
Serving God don't feel like

30:39.713 --> 30:41.549
it should be
a money-making opportunity.

30:41.715 --> 30:42.716
TAMMY: Yeah.

30:43.509 --> 30:45.594
You know,
I wanna do what he's doing.

30:46.011 --> 30:48.597
And I wanna sing
and not in a puppet voice.

30:48.764 --> 30:51.308
And I wanna talk about issues
that affect people's daily lives.

30:51.475 --> 30:52.977
And there's so much
that we don't talk about.

30:53.143 --> 30:54.186
There's so many secrets,

30:54.353 --> 30:57.523
and, you know, everyone says
I'm supposed to be tired,

30:58.148 --> 31:00.109
but I just wanna love people.

31:00.276 --> 31:01.694
You got me out of bed

31:01.777 --> 31:03.404
to talk to me about how you're not tired.

31:03.571 --> 31:05.406
Does that make sense to you?

31:07.491 --> 31:08.492
No.

31:09.535 --> 31:12.705
-Sorry.
-Night night, Tam. Take care.

31:12.871 --> 31:14.790
TAMMY: Good night, Mom.
I love you.

31:14.957 --> 31:15.958
Bye.

31:16.125 --> 31:17.459
Okay, bye-bye.

31:20.629 --> 31:21.630
FRED: Who was it?

31:24.550 --> 31:25.634
RACHEL: That was Tam.

31:25.718 --> 31:26.719
FRED: How is she?

31:26.802 --> 31:28.721
RACHEL: Well, it seems like
she's having some trouble

31:28.804 --> 31:30.306
with the pregnancy.
What'd I miss?

31:30.389 --> 31:31.473
JIM: ...a second childhood.

31:31.557 --> 31:32.808
FRED: I don't know.
The sound was off.

31:32.975 --> 31:34.393
You love kids, don't you?

31:34.476 --> 31:36.103
-You love children.
-COLONEL SANDERS: I do.

31:36.186 --> 31:39.607
I have five grandchildren
and 14 great-grandchildren.

31:39.773 --> 31:41.775
-Wow!
-

31:42.776 --> 31:44.695
I bet they're spoiled.
Do you spoil them?

31:52.953 --> 31:54.955
Oh, dear Lord God.

31:57.583 --> 32:01.170
What doors are you gonna
open up for me to walk through?

