55:54.143 --> 55:55.311
Right?

55:55.478 --> 55:56.562
Okay, get up on the pedestal.

55:56.729 --> 55:57.813
I am not getting up on the pedestal.

55:57.980 --> 55:59.065
-Come on, Grandma.
-Come on.

55:59.231 --> 56:00.566
-Come on.
-Don't push me.

56:02.109 --> 56:04.278
Isn't it fun?
We look like triplets.

56:04.445 --> 56:06.447
I look like a bear.

56:06.614 --> 56:08.199
You look like a beautiful bear.

56:08.657 --> 56:10.868
-Oh. It's too much.
-No.

56:10.951 --> 56:12.578
RACHEL: I already have a coat.

56:13.079 --> 56:14.622
I don't need it.

56:15.831 --> 56:18.918
Why are you so unwilling to accept
the love that God has for you?

56:20.002 --> 56:21.504
Can you pay for this?

56:21.670 --> 56:23.714
The pledges are rolling in, Mom.

56:23.881 --> 56:25.966
People really like the show

56:26.133 --> 56:29.970
and they're very happy to accept the love.

56:31.722 --> 56:33.182
Take the coat, Mom.

56:33.724 --> 56:35.935
Just take the coat.

56:36.018 --> 56:37.061
RACHEL: Well...

56:37.144 --> 56:38.938
TAMMY: Please, for me.

56:40.481 --> 56:44.902
Well, it is attractive,
and it's very, very warm.

56:46.153 --> 56:47.279
JIM: I just feel like a million dollars.

56:47.363 --> 56:49.156
WANDA: It looks great, Jim.
JIM: You think?

56:49.240 --> 56:50.407
Yeah, very subtle.

56:50.574 --> 56:52.409
I didn't feel a thing. Not a thing.

56:52.576 --> 56:54.286
And I played golf the next day.

56:54.453 --> 56:55.454
So, we'll have a girl's night.

56:55.538 --> 56:56.580
We'll go to Maciano's, get some pasta.

56:56.664 --> 56:57.665
SISSY: Yes, yes.

56:57.748 --> 56:59.416
-I love that place.
-Yeah? Oh, wait.

56:59.500 --> 57:02.002
You know, why don't you go ahead,
I'm gonna catch up.

57:02.211 --> 57:04.171
-I'm gonna go give Jim a kiss.
-Okay.

57:04.338 --> 57:05.339
See ya.

